ah, thereby situating it within contemporary discourses on liberal politics and community and creating the space for an alternative sociopolitical order to the nation-state, both as a local unit and a global system.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aGlobalizationxReligious aspectsxIslam. 0aIslamxUnity. 0aUmmah (Islam). 4aArea Studies : Middle East Studies. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Islam. 7aRELIGION / Islam / History.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848206440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438482064423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438482064/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles